Os higher blood within Etruria's bound, Though thy progenitors on either hand Long since o’er mighty armies bore. command, Yet thou dost not, as most are wont, contemn The nameless shoots of an inglorious stem, Men like myself‚ a freedman’s son; for thou Mak’st no account, who was his sire, or how A man was born, so long as inward worth And upright conduct dig-nify his birth. Thy stedfast creed it is, that, long before The slave-born Tullius kingly empire bore, Lived many a man, who ancestry had none, Yet by desert the amplest honours won, Whilst vile Laevinus, of the Valerian race , 1 That drove proud Tarquin from his pride of place, Was rated worth not one poor doit, and this Even by the populace, whose wont it is, As well thou know'st, unwisely to endow Unworthy men with dignities‚ to bow In foolish homage to a name, and gaze At rank and title with awestruck amaze.
